  "description": "A comprehensive benchmark dataset of 100+ molecules, atoms, ions, and radicals relevant to quantum chemistry and quantum physics, with high-level reference energies, geometries, excitation spectra, dipole moments, and thermochemical data. Includes closed-shell, open-shell, multi-reference, and transition metal systems. Used in benchmarking DFT, post-HF, and wavefunction-based methods across Psi4, PySCF, Quantum ESPRESSO, and CP2K. Curated from NIST CCCBDB, NIST ASD, peer-reviewed benchmarks, and supplemental computational datasets.",
